&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cDovL2Rmcy5kYXRhbm9kZS5jYWNoZS5yZXZvY2F0aW9uLnRpbWVvdXQubXM=&#34;&gt;dfs.datanode.cache.revocation.timeout.ms&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;900000&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;When the DFSClient reads from a block file which the DataNode is caching, the DFSClient can skip verifying checksums. The DataNode will keep the block file in cache until the client is done. If the client takes an unusually long time, though, the DataNode may need to evict the block file from the cache anyway. This value controls how long the DataNode will wait for the client to release a replica that it is reading without checksums.&lt;/td&gt;
