&lt;td&gt;-Xmx200m&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Java opts for the task processes. The following symbol, if present, will be interpolated: @taskid@ is replaced by current TaskID. Any other occurrences of &#39;@&#39; will go unchanged. For example, to enable verbose gc logging to a file named for the taskid in /tmp and to set the heap maximum to be a gigabyte, pass a &#39;value&#39; of: -Xmx1024m -verbose:gc -Xloggc:/tmp/@taskid@.gc Usage of -Djava.library.path can cause programs to no longer function if hadoop native libraries are used. These values should instead be set as part of LD_LIBRARY_PATH in the map / reduce JVM env using the mapreduce.map.env and mapreduce.reduce.env config settings.&lt;/td&gt;
