&lt;td&gt;ipc.client.fallback-to-simple-auth-allowed&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;false&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;When a client is configured to attempt a secure connection, but attempts to connect to an insecure server, that server may instruct the client to switch to SASL SIMPLE (unsecure) authentication. This setting controls whether or not the client will accept this instruction from the server. When false (the default), the client will not allow the fallback to SIMPLE authentication, and will abort the connection.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
